==English==
===Noun===
'''precipitation'''
# A [[hurried]] [[headlong]] [[fall]].
#{{chemistry}} A [[reaction]] that leads to the [[formation]] of a [[heavier]] [[solid]] in a [[lighter]] [[liquid]]; the [[precipitate]] so formed at the bottom of the container.
# Any form of [[water]] (i.e. [[rain]], [[hail]], [[snow]] or [[sleet]]) falling from the [[sky]].
#{{figurative}} [[unwise|Unwise]] or [[rash]] [[rapidity]]; [[sudden]] [[haste]].
#:had acted with some ''precipitation'' and had probably started out upon a wild-goose chase  -- [[Wikipedia:Dorothy Sayers|Dorothy Sayers]]
